CE="Verdana,Arial">Because the board has been growing a lot lately, the immature public has been growing too. This unfortunately forced us to start with adding rules to the board.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
When you post on the Erollisi Marr EzBoard after the day/time this post has been written you agree with these new rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
You are a guest, act like one.<br>
<br>
1) If you start a flame thread in any other forum than <A href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames, Dragons and Planes</a>, the administrator or moderators will move it to the &quot;right&quot; forum or just delete it (up to us). Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
2) If you reply with a flame in any other forum than <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames, Dragons and Planes</a>, the administrator or moderators will delete it. Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
3) Anonymous flaming is NEVER allowed. This board allows unregistered users because some people do not know how, or do not want/care to register. If you flame anonymous your posts will be deleted and you will be banned (read “banishment”)<br>
<br>
4) Mule EzBoard accounts are NOT allowed. Your EzBoard accounts created to flame people will get banned (read “banishment”) including all the other accounts that has been used by you. If nobody knows who you are, and you are only known to flame people you will fall into this category. The administrator and moderators may judge for their own if your account is a mule EzBoard account or not.<br>
<br>
5) Anything deemed sexually or racially discriminating, or of an equally offensive nature will be deleted and the administrator and moderators may choose to ban the author (depends on the post).<br>
<br>
6) Adult material is NOT allowed. Pornographic stories, pictures, violent stories, etc. are NOT allowed. Post them and they will get deleted. Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
7) The administrator and moderators are allowed to delete and modify posts/threads and/or ban you without giving you, or anyone else, an explanation.<br>
<br>
8) The administrator and moderators may add/change/remove rules whenever they please. When you post after these changes you agree with these new rules.<br>
<br>
9) Forums may have specific rules. If you post in those forums you agree with those rules.<br>
<br>
10) The administrator and moderators are allowed to “close” a thread whenever they please. They don't have to give you or anyone else an explanation. If you try to continue the “closed” thread with creating a new thread, this thread will be deleted. Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
11) Re-submitting of deleted post (does not matter if you're the author or not) will get you banned (read “banishment”).<br>
<br>
12) Do not use offensive usernames and/or pictures.<br>
<br>
13) Size of personal pictures and signatures are restricted. Please read: <A href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrmessageboardrules.showMessage?topicID=5.topic>Rules of personal pictures & signature size</a>. If your personal picture and/or signature is larger than allowed, your posts may get deleted. So please, pay attention.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Banishment<br>
<br>
Since you can swap from ISP (and thus IP address) in an eyewink we have added a few rules.<br>
<br>
1) The administrator and moderators are allowed to do everything to get you banned from this board. Not only may they ban your IP, but they are also allowed to publicize your IP address that allows people to write complains to your ISP (Internet Service Provider).<br>
<br>
2) The administrator and moderators are allowed to write all your information (IP address, other EzBoard accounts, the guild you’re in) on the board so other people can prevent that you will be ruining their board also.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I hope everyone understand why we added these rules. Let's continue having fun and stop the unnecessary flames.<br>
